line_1: Their fat the butchers pleas'd, but me their dung.
line_2: Oft have I prais'd them as they stalk'd along,

line_1: " The tawdry child of sordid dung!
line_2: "Forget you, then, from whence you sprung,

line_1: Above the sordid miser's glitt'ring dung,
line_2: On vulgar pride from vaunted heroes sprung;

line_1: And feeds with Pleasure on its native Dung.
line_2: Unchang'd admires the Ordure, whence it sprung,

line_1: Cleaves, tho' a Monarch, to his native dung,
line_2: And venerates the soil from whence he sprung.
